    "The formula is as follows:P (w) = e (P (w) w ′ e (P (w ′) if w is in the top-k 0 otherwise(2)where:w: is the word being sampled, P (w): is the probability of word,V: is the vocabulary of possible words.Top-p sampling, also known as nucleus sampling, selects the smallest set of words whose combined probability surpasses a predetermined threshold p. This method is defined by the following mathematical formula [50]:P (w) = 1 w ′ ∈V:P (w ′)≥p P (w ′)(3)where:w ′ ∈V:P (w ′)≥p P (w ′): sum of probabilities Furthermore, we integrated an additional set of configuration options into our methodology, specifically the \"temperature\" parameter.",
    "This parameter significantly influences the model's calculated probability distribution for the upcoming token prediction.",
    "Acting as a scaling mechanism within the softmax layer of the transformer models, the temperature value modulates the degree of randomness in the output.",
    "Elevating the temperature parameter enhances the diversity in the output by increasing randomness, whereas diminishing the temperature narrows down the selection of potential words, leading to more predictable text.",
    "This flexibility allows us to achieve the desired balance between creativity and coherence in our scenario development [51] [48]."
